Sentencas: Sintering temperature dependences of specific surface area, pore size distribution, and pore volume of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3 ceramics prepared using the Pechini method have been evaluated from the adsorption isotherms of N2 gas at -195.8 degrees C.
Titulo: Evaluation of Specific Surface Area and Pore Size Distribution of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3 Ceramics Prepared using Pechini Method by N2 Adsorption Method-Optimization of Sintering Temperature as Cathode Material of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The specific surface area decreased almost linearly with increasing sintering temperature showing that preparation of the ceramic specimens with controlled surface area is possible by sintering temperature.
Titulo: Evaluation of Specific Surface Area and Pore Size Distribution of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3 Ceramics Prepared using Pechini Method by N2 Adsorption Method-Optimization of Sintering Temperature as Cathode Material of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The pore size distribution, evaluated by BJH method, showed two peaks around 2.5 and 250 nm with narrow FWHM for the specimen sintered at 900 degrees C.
Titulo: Evaluation of Specific Surface Area and Pore Size Distribution of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3 Ceramics Prepared using Pechini Method by N2 Adsorption Method-Optimization of Sintering Temperature as Cathode Material of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Although both the peaks were maintained in the specimens sintered at 1000 degrees C and 1100 degrees C, their intensity decreased with increasing sintering temperature, indicating decrease of pore volume.
Titulo: Evaluation of Specific Surface Area and Pore Size Distribution of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3 Ceramics Prepared using Pechini Method by N2 Adsorption Method-Optimization of Sintering Temperature as Cathode Material of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: It has been revealed that sintering below 1100 degrees C is necessary to prepare LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3 ceramics with pore volume maintained, which is suitable for SOFC cathode material.
Titulo: Evaluation of Specific Surface Area and Pore Size Distribution of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3 Ceramics Prepared using Pechini Method by N2 Adsorption Method-Optimization of Sintering Temperature as Cathode Material of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
